<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0490</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow in New England, Great Lakes; Warm in Midwest, Atlantic States</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow ushered in Thanksgiving week in New England today, while
parts of the Midwest and the mid-Atlantic states enjoyed
unseasonably mild weather.
   Skies were clear over much of the nation early today, but snow
fell in Portland, Maine; Albany, N.Y.; and Boston. Up to 4 inches
of snow was predicted today across northern Vermont and New
Hampshire, and lesser amounts were expected in upstate New York and
Massachusetts.
   Snow also was expected in northern Wisconsin and perhaps
elsewhere in the Great Lakes region.
   Unseasonably warm weather in Iowa and surrounding states over
the weekend was expected to linger into this morning, but fade away
as winds shifted to the north, bringing more seasonable
temperatures.
   Virginia, Maryland, Delaware and West Virginia were expected to
get a respite from fall, with high temperatures climbing into the
60s. But a cold front was expected to move in tonight.
   Temperatures a much as 25 degrees above normal for mid-November
were recorded in the upper Plains states and upper Mississippi
Valley over the weekend, and Denver had its warmest November day in
117 years Sunday.
   Denver's 79-degree reading eclipsed by 2 degrees a standard that
has stood since 1897.
   Other record highs Sunday included Oakland, Calif., 75;
Dickinson, N.D., 61; Goodland, Kan., 77; and Grand Island, Neb., 72.
   The day's high was 96 at Camp Pendleton, Calif.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EST today:
   _EAST: Albany, N.Y., 31 snow; Atlanta 46 fair; Boston 32 snow;
Charleston, S.C., 41 fair; Chattanooga 40 fair; Cincinnati 49
partly cloudy; Cleveland 49 cloudy; Detroit 45 windy; Hatteras 48
fair; Jacksonville 45 fair; Key West 72 fair; Miami 66 fair; New
York 42 windy; Philadelphia 43 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 45 cloudy;
Portland, Maine, 31 snow; Richmond 45 fair; Tampa 61 partly cloudy;
Washington, D.C. 43 partly cloudy.
   _CENTRAL: Birmingham 39 fair; Bismarck 41 fair; Chicago 48
windy; Denver 46 fair; Des Moines 48 fair; Indianapolis 48 fair;
Kansas City 48 fair; Little Rock 50 fair; Louisville 51 partly
cloudy; Memphis 53 fair; Nashville 50 fair; New Orleans 56 partly
cloudy; North Platte 33 fair; Oklahoma City 54 fair; Omaha 39 fair;
Rapid City 46 fair; St. Louis 55 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 38
partly cloudy; Sault Ste. Marie 38 cloudy; San Antonio 60 foggy.
   _WEST: Albuquerque 40 fair; Anchorage 13 fair; Boise 31 fair;
Casper 45 fair; Fairbanks 00 snow; Great Falls 49 cloudy; Honolulu
74 partly cloudy; Las Vegas 53 fair; Los Angeles 71 fair; Medford
34 fair; Pendleton 49 fair; Phoenix 73 partly cloudy; Portland,
Ore., 47 foggy; Reno 33 fair; Salt Lake City 33 foggy; San Diego 73
partly cloudy; San Francisco 54 fair.
   _INTERNATIONAL: Calgary 30 partly cloudy; Montreal 28 snow;
Ottawa 30 snow; Regina 34 windy; Toronto 41 rain; Winnipeg 32
partly cloudy.
