<SECOND>PM-US-Lebanon,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ambassador Heading Home Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Ambassador John McCarthy is on his way
home after presenting his credentials to Rene Moawad, the new
president of Lebanon.
   McCarthy and all other American diplomats were withdrawn from
the Middle Eastern country in early September amid civil strife
between Christian and Moslem factions.
   The embassy was put in the hands of Lebanese guards. It is not
being reopened yet, and McCarthy is on his way home after some 28
hours in Lebanon, a U.S. official, who declined to be identified,
said today.
   The ambassador presented his credentials Saturday at Mouawad in
the president's summer home at Ehden and went to Syria en route to
Washington.
