<SECOND>PM-Bakker Ministry,0264</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tammy Bakker Denies Tabloid Story That She Seeks Divorce</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tammy Faye Bakker says although she is
afraid of flying she will take a plane to Minnesota to spend
Thanksgiving with her jailed husband.
   In a Sunday sermon to some 50 supporters, she also blasted a
weekly tabloid that said she would divorce Jim Bakker, the former
televangelist convicted last month of fraud.
   ``There's no truth whatsoever to it,'' she said, adding that
readers of such ``rag magazines'' are ``like dogs chasing garbage
trucks _ yuck!''
   Without providing details, Mrs. Bakker said a promising deal for
a new Orlando home for Jim and Tammy Ministries fell through last
week.
   ``Satan is trying to stop us from holding services in Florida,''
she said. She told supporters she continues to believe that ``God
has a place in Orlando for us somewhere.''
   The owner of the Shoppers World mall that houses the Bakkers'
storefront church has ordered them out by the end of the month,
saying he hasn't been paid.
   Bakker is serving a 45-year sentence in a federal prison in
Rochester, Minn., for defrauding followers of the former PTL Club
of $3.7 million.
   Mrs. Bakker said she is afraid of flying but will make the trip
Thursday because she is eager to see her husband. She sobbed as she
told how Bakker must make collect telephone calls, calling it
``very embarrassing for a man who paid all his bills for so many
people for so many years and gave, gave, gave.''
