<FIRST>r a AM-Bush-Hecklers     11-20 0352</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bush-Hecklers,330</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hecklers Confront Bush on Aid to El Salvador</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-US-Salvador, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is President Bush's exchange with hecklers
Monday over U.S. support for El Salvador. The exchange took place
at a fund-raising luncheon for Rep. Lynn Martin, R-Ill.
   A woman in a broad-brimmed hat at the front of the crowd of
2,000 began shouting, ``Why are we supporting El Salvador?'' The
crowd began booing her.
   ``Just a minute. The lady asked a good question,'' Bush said.
``Let me repeat and I'll give her an answer if you promise to be
quiet after I answer. You promise? Word of honor? All right, good.
   ``The question is, `Why are we supporting El Salvador?'''
reiterated Bush.
   ``No, the question is why are we killing priests in El
Salvador?'' a second woman shouted.
   ``The answer is we're not and you be quiet and hear the answer
to your question,'' he said sternly.
   ``We are supporting El Salvador because it had certifiably free
elections. President Cristiani is trying to _ '' Bush said,
stopping as the women began shouting him down. Police led the two
women out of the room.
   A minute later, a young man began shouting at the front of the
crowd: ``End the war! Stop the repression in El Salvador!''
   Bush said, ``Look at this guy! Look at this guy! What's your
position?''
   As the man was hustled away, Bush said, ``Let me just say a word
about El Salvador and maybe it will help.
   ``It was the FMLN, the Marxist-Leninist FMLN, that shot its way
into the middle of El Salvador trying to disrupt Salvador's
democracy. And President Cristiani told me on the phone that they
will do everything they can to bring to justice _ whether they are
from the right or the left _ those who wantonly murdered those
priests.
   ``But we must not pull our support away from a freely elected
democratic government. Now, who's next? All I ask is equal time,''
said Bush.
   The crowd cheered.
   There were also protesters at the back of the hall and one of
them was ejected, too.
</TEXT>
