<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Walesa-Degree     11-20 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Walesa-Degree,0156</SECOND>
<HEAD>Providence College Must Try Again to Give Walesa Degree</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Polish Solidarity leader Lech Walesa is
still without the honorary degree Providence College awarded him in
1982. Plans to give it to him fell through this weekend, a school
spokeswoman said Monday.
   The Rev. John G. McGreevy, vice president for institutional
relations at Providence, was to present the doctorate of laws
degree and academic hood to Walesa on Sunday in Doylestown, Pa.,
before a Mass in Walesa's honor at the Church at the National
Shrine of Czestochowa.
   But Ann Manchester-Molak of Providence College said McGreevy met
Walesa only briefly and did not get a chance to present him the
degree.
   ```He did get to meet him, but he was taken away so quickly he
didn't get a chance to do it,'' said Manchester.
   Walesa flew to Venezuela on Monday after a weeklong visit in the
United States.
</TEXT>
