<FIRST>r w AM-Kmart-Recall     11-20 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-K mart-Recall,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>K mart Recalls Air Fresheners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The K mart Corp. is voluntarily recalling
several thousand air freshening devices because they pose a fire
hazard, according to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
   K mart last week recalled 15,000 Ceramic Potpourri Houses
because the tealight candle sold with them burns too hot and poses
a risk of fire, the agency said.
   There have been at least 12 incidents since June where the
houses caught fire, resulting in minor property damage. There have
been no reported injuries, the company said.
   Consumers should return the houses, numbered 32-67-47, to any K
mart store for a full refund or replacement of either the houses or
the candle.
