<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Monday he will
nominate David C. Fields, now U.S. ambassador to the Central
African Republic, to be director of the Office of Foreign Missions
in the State Department.
   Fields, 52, is a career foreign service officer. He would
succeed James E. Nolan Jr.
