for enforcement and tarrif affairs. Nunez, 47, of San Diego,
Calif., is currently a lawyer in private practice.
   Bush also said he would nominate former Sen. William D. Hathaway
of Maine to be a Federal Maritime Commissioner. A Washington
attorney since 1979, Hathaway, 65, would succeed Thomas F. Moakley.
   Hathaway, a Democrat, was in the Senate from 1973 to 1978.
