<FIRST>r a AM-Millionaire-Slaying     11-20 0313</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Millionaire-Slaying,0327</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wife of Millionaire Sentenced to Life For Slaying</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOAN THOMPSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman convicted of hiring a gang to murder her
millionaire husband three years ago should be sentenced to life in
prison, a jury recommended Monday.
   Jurors, who could have recommended the death penalty for Joyce
Cohen, reached their decision after deliberating about 40 minutes.
   Dade County Circuit Judge Fredricka Smith set sentencing for
Tuesday. She is not bound by the jury's recommendation.
   The same panel on Thursday found Mrs. Cohen, 39, guilty of
first-degree murder, conspiracy to commit murder and using a
firearm in commission of the March 7, 1986, of Stanley Cohen.
   She was convicted of offering three hit men $100,000 to kill her
husband.
   Prosecutors said she supplied a map of their Coconut Grove home,
disconnected alarms, unlocked the door and gave them her husband's
gun.
   Prosecutors said the marriage had soured, and that the former
secretary feared a divorce would end her jet-set lifestyle.
   Defense attorneys said the killings were due to Cohen's drug
connections, but his relatives said that was a lie.
   In the penalty phase of the trial Monday, defense witnesses
testified Mrs. Cohen had been sexually molested during a miserable
childhood.
   ``Her mother, a prostitute, died when she was about 12 and she
virtually was never raised by a mother,'' said Dr. Lawrence Cohn, a
psychiatrist.
   A friend of the defendant, Claudia Smith, said she did not
believe Mrs. Cohen could harm anyone.
   ``I know you found her guilty,'' a sobbing Mrs. Smith told the
jury, ``but I and a lot of people have stood by her and I am still
and so are her other friends.''
   Prosecutor John Kastrenakes said Mrs. Cohen chose ``to plan and
to carry out ... a brutal, heinous murder of her husband while he
lay sleeping in his own bed.''
</TEXT>
