<HEAD>Coal Production Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 20.7
million tons during the week ending Nov. 11, up slightly from the
20.4 million tons produced in the previous week, the Department of
Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19.7 million tons in the same
week last year, according to the department's Energy Information
Administration.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 841.4 million tons,
5.8 percent above last year's production at this time, the agency
said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
